-- Posco Assan Gets $209 Million Loan for Turkish Plant
-- B y   E r c a n   E r s o y
-- 2012-05-08T13:57:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-08/posco-assan-gets-209-million-loan-for-turkish-plant-correct-.html
Posco (005490)  Assan, a joint venture between
Posco, South Korea’s biggest steelmaker, and Turkish Kibar
Holding AS, got a $209.3 million loan for its $350 million
stainless steel plant investment in Kocaeli province in
northwestern  Turkey .  Posco Assan signed the loan agreement with ING Groep NV,
HSBC Holdings Plc,  Korea Development Bank  and SMBC, according to
an e-mailed statement from ING’s Istanbul unit ING Bank AS
today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ercan Ersoy in Istanbul at 
 eersoy@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
